				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$J_{\mathrm{s}} = \frac{{dV}}{{dt}}\frac{1}{{\Omega A_{\mathrm{n}}}} = \frac{{\nu A_{\mathrm{w}}}}{{\Omega A_{\mathrm{n}}}} = \frac{{\nu \Phi _{\mathrm{w}}^2}}{{4\Omega\Phi _{\mathrm{n}}\delta _{\mathrm{s}}}}$$\end{document}Js=dVdt1ΩAn=νAwΩAn=νΦw24ΩΦnδswhere Ω is the atomic volume of Al (1.66 × 10−29 m3), An is the cross-sectional area of the surface pre-melting layer at the neck with a nominal surface layer thickness δs = 3 Å, Aw is the cross-section area of the nanowire. The resultant Js = 4.5 × 1022 m−2 s−1.

For elemental metals, the thermomigration flux contribution JT32,33 is written as2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
